57    /**
58    * A symbol table for people that want to use Closure Compiler as an indexer.
59    *
60    * Contains an index of all the symbols in the code within a compilation
61    * job. The API is designed for people who want to visit all the symbols, rather
62    * than people who want to lookup a specific symbol by a certain key.
63    *
64    * We can use this to combine different types of symbol tables. For example,
65    * one class might have a {@code StaticSymbolTable} of all variable references,
66    * and another class might have a {@code StaticSymbolTable} of all type names
67    * in JSDoc comments. This class allows you to combine them into a unified
68    * index.
69    *
70    * Most passes build their own "partial" symbol table that implements the same
71    * interface (StaticSymbolTable, StaticSlot, and friends). Individual compiler
72    * passes usually need more or less metadata about the certainty of symbol
73    * information. Building a complete symbol table with all the necessary metadata
74    * for all passes would be too slow. However, as long as these "partial" symbol
75    * tables implement the proper interfaces, we should be able to add them to this
76    * symbol table to make it more complete.
77    *
78    * If clients want fast lookup, they should build their own wrapper around
79    * this symbol table that indexes symbols or references by the desired lookup
80    * key.
81    *
82    * By design, when this symbol table creates symbols for types, it tries
83    * to mimic the symbol table you would get in an OO language. For example,
84    * the "type Foo" and "the constructor that creates objects of type Foo"
85    * are the same symbol. The types of "Foo.prototype" and "new Foo()" also
86    * have the same symbol. Although JSCompiler internally treats these as
87    * distinct symbols, we assume that most clients will not care about
88    * the distinction.
89    *
90    * @see #addSymbolsFrom For more information on how to write plugins for this
91    * symbol table.
92    *
93    * @author nicksantos@google.com (Nick Santos)
94    */
